AGI - The spokesman of the Russian Foreign Ministry, Maria Zakharova, > has defined offensive, scandalous and completely false the "blaspheme inventions" > and the analogies quoted by President Sergio Mattarella>, who had compared the Russian invasion of Ukraine to the project of the Third Reich> in Europe.
&nbsp;
On February 5, during a lecture at the University of Marseille, the Italian president "made several offensive statements" on Russia, Zakharova recalled, as reported by the agency Tass. "He traced scandalous and frankly false historical parallelisms between the Russian Federation and, as he said, Nazi Germany," Zakharova explained in a briefing with the press, adding that in this regard it is "impossible even to pronounce".
&nbsp;
Mattarella continued the spokesman, "said that Russia's actions in Ukraine are of a similar nature to the Third Reich project in Europe". According to Zakharova, "it is strange and crazy to hear such blasphemous inventions from the president of Italy, a country that knows firsthand what fascism really is."
&nbsp;
"Our country was subjected to a monstrous attack by Hitler's Germany," said Zakharova. "Our country was not only able to expel the enemy from its territory, but also freed Europe from Nazism and fascism," the spokesman added. Moreover, the Italian president "would have to reflect on the fact that today Italy, together with other countries of NATO, is equipping the terrorist and neo-Nazi regime of Kiev in Ukraine with modern and deadly weapons, thus unconditionally supporting the criminal regime in all its crimes", Zakharova observed.
&nbsp;
"All Mattarella said during his lecture at the University of Marseille," the spokesman concluded, "offends the memory not only of all Italians who fought against fascism during the Great Patriotic War and their descendants both in Russia and in Italy, but also of all those who know history and do not accept these unacceptable and criminal analogies". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> The Quirinal: Mattarella absolutely serene, refer to the speech</h2>
The President of the Republic is absolutely serene and refers to the reading of the text delivered in Marseille. This is what emerges from the Quirinal after the attacks of the Kremlin to the President of the Republic. "The authoritarian phenomena took over in some countries, attracted by the fable that despotic and illiberal regimes were more effective in protecting national interests," said the Head of State, "the result was the focus of a climate of conflict - instead of cooperation - while in the awareness of having to face and solve problems at a larger scale. But instead of cooperation, the criterion of domination prevailed. And they were conquest wars. This was the project of the Third Reich in Europe. Today's Russian aggression to Ukraine is of this nature."
&nbsp;
<h2>Solidity Meloni, "the insults a&nbsp;Mattarella&nbsp;offend the Nation"></h2>
"The insults of the spokesman of the Russian Foreign Ministry, which defined the words of the President of the Republic, Sergio&nbsp; Mattarella, offend the entire Italian nation, which the Head of State represents. I express my full solidarity, as well as that of the entire government, to President &nbsp; Mattarella, who has always firmly supported the condemnation of the aggression perpetrated against Ukraine." The President of the Council, Giorgia&nbsp;Meloni.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Schlein, "solidarity of the PD after the Moscow attacks" >/h2>
"Solidarity to the President of the Republic Sergio&nbsp;Mattarella, attacked by the Moscow government for having condemned with force and without means terms the aggression of Russia against Ukraine. The democratic community - the secretary of the Pd Elly&nbsp;Schlein - is fully recognized in the words and action of the Head of State, custodian of the Constitution and democracy. He goes my personal gratitude and that of the Democratic Party."

